<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-04T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-04T21:00:00-05:00" n="10" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d10">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5686: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-05T10:00:00+08:00">January 5, 1933—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 5—2:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>15. Following from American Consul General at Harbin: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“January 4, 11 a.m.</p>
                                <list>
                                    <label>1.</label>
                                    <item>Entire east line Chinese Eastern Railway now occupied by
                                        Japanese troops which practically without meeting opposition
                                        reached Suifenho January 3d.</item>
                                    <label>2.</label>
                                    <item>Morishima, Japanese Consul General, informed me that he
                                        reached agreement December 29th with local Soviet Consul
                                        General to the effect that Soviet Government would not
                                        object to Japanese troops going as far as Suifenho. Soviet
                                        Consulate General confirms this.”</item>
                                </list>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>